# WIA Inner Circle — Cursor Rules
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

## Project
Landing page de captación de leads para la comunidad privada WIA Inner Circle
(World Institutional Assets). Trading · Negocios · Inversiones · Mentalidad.
Operado desde Dubai por Santiago.

## Stack
- Next.js 14 (App Router)
- TypeScript (strict)
- Tailwind CSS v3
- Framer Motion v11
- No backend yet — form logs to console, ready to wire

## Brand
- Background:  #050505  (almost black)
- Primary CTA:  #D6FF00  (neon lime)
- Typography:   Bebas Neue (headings) + Inter (body)
- Tone:         Luxury · Minimal · Apple / Porsche aesthetic
- Language:     Spanish (es)

## File structure
wia-inner-circle/
├── app/
│   ├── layout.tsx        ← metadata, viewport, font imports
│   ├── page.tsx          ← assembles all sections in order
│   └── globals.css       ← base styles + Tailwind @layer components
├── components/
│   ├── Nav.tsx           ← fixed nav, fades bg on scroll, desktop links
│   ├── Hero.tsx          ← fullscreen split: copy left, photo right
│   ├── Results.tsx       ← 2-col: Bookmap photo + copy + stats
│   ├── Statement.tsx     ← fullscreen parallax: steering wheel photo
│   ├── Gallery.tsx       ← 12-col desktop grid, 2-col mobile
│   ├── Interstitial.tsx  ← 70vh parallax photo with caption
│   ├── Form.tsx          ← lead capture form, controlled, success state
│   └── Footer.tsx        ← minimal 3-col footer
├── lib/
│   ├── constants.ts      ← ALL copy, image paths, colors, form options
│   └── motion.ts         ← shared Framer Motion variants (fadeUp, scaleIn…)
└── public/images/        ← all photos as .jpeg files

## Images (public/images/)
- hero.jpeg            Santiago terraza Dubai Marina de pie
- bookmap.jpeg         Bookmap Order Flow screen (Results section)
- steering-wheel.jpeg  Lambo STO cockpit + Rolex (Statement section)
- gwagon.jpeg          G-Wagon Onyx naranja (Gallery G1, large left)
- urus.jpeg            Lamborghini Urus turquesa (Gallery G2, top right)
- lambo-sto.jpeg       Lamborghini Huracán STO parking (Gallery G3)
- desk-day.jpeg        Santiago desk vista Dubai día (Gallery G4)
- lambo-day.jpeg       Lambo exterior día (Interstitial section)

## Rules for Cursor
1. NEVER recreate, edit, crop, or stylize photos.
   Only move them between sections or change objectPosition.

2. ALL copy and paths live in lib/constants.ts.
   Edit copy there, not inside components.

3. ALL Framer Motion variants live in lib/motion.ts.
   Import from there; don't define inline variants.

4. Use Tailwind utility classes as first choice.
   Fall back to inline styles only for dynamic values (useTransform outputs).

5. Shared CSS patterns (.btn-lime, .label, .input-field, .photo-frame, .section-pad)
   are defined in globals.css @layer components. Use them.

6. Animations:
   - Entrance: fadeUp, scaleIn from lib/motion.ts
   - Parallax: useScroll + useTransform (only in Statement, Interstitial)
   - Nothing excessive — no bounce, no 3D, no color flashes

7. When adding a new section:
   a. Create component in /components/
   b. Add image path to IMAGES in lib/constants.ts
   c. Add copy to constants.ts
   d. Import in app/page.tsx

8. Form (Form.tsx):
   - State is controlled (useState<FormData>)
   - handleSubmit logs to console — wire to your API here
   - TODO comment marks the integration point

9. Responsive breakpoints (Tailwind):
   - Desktop first
   - max-md (< 768px): single column, reduced padding
   - max-sm (< 640px): form rows collapse

10. No gradients, no fake 3D, no AI art, no emojis in UI.
    Keep it clean and premium.

## Common tasks
- Change hero photo:       update IMAGES.hero in lib/constants.ts
- Change section copy:     edit the relevant constant in lib/constants.ts
- Add a new gallery photo: add to IMAGES, update photos array in Gallery.tsx
- Wire the form:           replace console.log in Form.tsx handleSubmit
- Add a section:           new .tsx in /components, import in page.tsx
- Change lime color:       update --lime in globals.css AND tailwind.config.ts
